different ways to writing function in javascript

A) Factory functions

1) function declaration

function square(x){
return x*x;
}


2) Function Expression

const square = function(x){
return x*x
}

3) Arrow function Expression

const square = (x) => {
return x*x;
}

4) inline arrow funciton
( (x) => x*x )


5) Generator function

function* square(x){
return x*x
}


B) Constructor functions


1) New function

const numberA = numberA,
const numberB = numberB

const sumFunction = new Funtion(numberA, numberB, 'return numberA + numberB');

sumFunction(8,9) // 17
